Graham Douglas, a former Minister of Labour and Productivity, is dead. DailyTrust confirmed that the former Minister passed on Monday at a hospital in Abuja, FCT. Graham-Douglas served as minister of Labour, Employment and Productivity under Olusegun Obasanjoâ€™s administration. The deceased, in 1989, was appointed as the Minister for Social Development, Youths and Sports by the Military President, Ibrahim Babangida. He lost to former President Olusegun Obasanjo in the presidential primaries of the PDP in 1998.